title: Friday the 13th
text: A group of young adults discover a boarded up Camp Crystal Lake, where they soon encounter Jason Voorhees and his deadly intentions.

title: Bride Wars

title: Ran
text: An elderly lord abdicates to his three sons, and the two corrupt ones turn against him.

text: James Bond investigates the hijacking of British and Russian submarines carrying nuclear warheads with the help of a KGB agent whose lover he killed.

title: Grimm

title: Revolver
text: Gambler Jake Green enters into a game with potentially deadly consequences.

text: A paranoid, secretive surveillance expert has a crisis of conscience when he suspects that a couple he is spying on will be murdered.

text: Only a short time after the first raid, Rama goes undercover with the thugs of Jakarta and plans to bring down the syndicate and uncover the corruption within his police force.

text: The greatest Olympic Wrestling Champion brother team joins Team Foxcatcher led by multimillionaire sponsor John E. du Pont as they train for the 1988 games in Seoul - a union that leads to unlikely circumstances.

title: War
text: An FBI Agent seeks vengeance on a mysterious assassin known as "Rogue" who murdered his partner.

text: After a young man's premonition of a deadly race-car crash helps saves the lives of his peers, Death sets out to collect those who evaded their end.

title: Runaway Bride
text: A reporter is assigned to write a story about a woman who has left a string of fiances at the altar.

title: Lady and the Tramp
text: The romantic tale of a sheltered uptown Cocker Spaniel dog and a streetwise downtown Mutt.

title: Arlington Road
text: A college professor begins to suspect that his neighbour is a terrorist.

title: The Heartbreak Kid
text: A newly wed man who believes he's just gotten hitched to the perfect woman encounters another lady on his honeymoon.

text: A psychological thriller centered around a black-ops interrogator and an FBI agent who press a suspect terrorist into divulging the location of three nuclear weapons set to detonate in the U.S.

title: WarGames
text: A young man finds a back door into a military central computer in which reality is confused with game-playing, possibly starting World War III.

title: Doctor Dolittle
text: A Doctor finds out that he can understand what animals are saying. And the animals find out that he understands.

title: Elephant
text: Several ordinary high school students go through their daily routine as two others prepare for something more malevolent.

title: My Week with Marilyn
text: Colin Clark, an employee of Sir

title: Saw VI
text: Agent Strahm is dead and framed while Hoffman continues John's legacy while Jill carries out John's final request.

title: Half Nelson
text: An inner-city junior high school teacher with a drug habit forms an unlikely friendship with one of his students after she discovers his secret.

text: An invisible and mysterious force field descends upon a small fictional town in the United States, trapping residents inside, cut off from the rest of civilization. The trapped townsfolk must discover the secrets and purpose of the "dome" and its origins, while coming to learn more than they ever knew about each other.

title: Superman II
text: Superman agrees to sacrifice his powers to marry Lois, unaware that three Kryptonian criminals he inadvertently released are conquering Earth.

text: Agent 007 and the Japanese secret service ninja force must find and stop the true culprit of a series of spacejackings before nuclear war is provoked.

text: On the run after murdering a man, accountant William Blake encounters a strange North American man named Nobody who prepares him for his journey into the spiritual world.

text: A "National Geographic" film crew is taken hostage by an insane hunter, who takes them along on his quest to capture the world's largest - and deadliest - snake.

title: Octopussy
text: A fake FabergÃ© egg and a fellow agent's death lead James Bond to uncover an international jewel-smuggling operation, headed by the mysterious Octopussy, being used to disguise a nuclear attack on N.A.T.O. forces.

title: Teen Wolf
text: A somewhat awkward teen is attacked by a werewolf and inherits the curse himself, as well as the enemies that come with it.

text: A chance encounter between a disgraced music-business executive and a young singer-songwriter new to Manhattan turns into a promising collaboration between the two talents.

title: Ghost Dog: The Way of the Samurai
text: An African American mafia hit man who models himself after the samurai of old finds himself targeted for death by the mob.

text: A misunderstood boy takes on ghosts, zombies and grown-ups to save his town from a centuries-old curse.

title: Jobs
text: The story of Steve Jobs' ascension from college dropout into one of the most revered creative entrepreneurs of the 20th century.

title: Hidalgo
text: In 1890, a down-and-out cowboy and his horse travel to Arabia to compete in a deadly cross desert horse race.

title: Beasts of the Southern Wild
text: Faced with both her hot-tempered father's fading health and melting ice-caps that flood her ramshackle bayou community and unleash ancient aurochs, six-year-old Hushpuppy must learn the ways of courage and love.

title: Breaking Bad
text: Walt goes on the run. Jesse is taken hostage. Skyler believes it's time to tell Flynn the truth.

title: Goon
text: Labeled an outcast by his brainy family, a bouncer overcomes long odds to lead a team of under performing misfits to semi-pro hockey glory, beating the crap out of everything that stands in his way.

title: The Man with the Golden Gun
text: Bond is led to believe that he is targeted by the world's most expensive assassin and must hunt him down to stop him.

title: The Kite Runner
text: After spending years in California, Amir returns to his homeland in Afghanistan to help his old friend Hassan, whose son is in trouble.

title: Frankenweenie
text: Young Victor conducts a science experiment to bring his beloved dog Sparky back to life, only to face unintended, sometimes monstrous, consequences.

title: Misfits
text: A group of young offenders doing community service get struck by lightning during a storm, and begin to develop superpowers.

title: Terra Nova
text: Centers on the Shannons, an ordinary family from 2149 when the planet is dying who are transported back 85 million years to prehistoric Earth where they join Terra Nova, a colony of humans with a second chance to build a civilization.

title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles
text: A group of mutated turtle warriors must emerge from the shadows to protect New York City from an uprising criminal gang of ninjas.

title: Sweet November
text: Nelson is a man devoted to his advertising career in San Francisco. One day, while taking a driving test at the DMV...

title: The Frighteners
text: After a tragic car accident that killed his wife, a man discovers he can communicate with the dead to con people but when a demonic spirit appears, he may be the only one who can stop it from killing the living and the dead.

title: West Side Story
text: Two youngsters from rival New York City gangs fall in love, but tensions between their respective friends build toward tragedy.

title: It's Complicated
text: When attending their son's college graduation, a couple reignite the spark in their relationship...but the complicated fact is they're divorced and he's remarried.

title: Universal Soldier
text: Luc and Scott were killed in Vietnam, but the army has a secret project for reanimating dead people as near-perfect soldiers.

title: The Ring Two
text: Six months after the incidents involving the lethal videotape, new clues prove that there is a new evil lurking in the darkness.

title: While You Were Sleeping
text: Ticket collecting romantic pretends to be engaged to an unconscious man but can't fool his brother

title: A Good Year
text: A British investment broker inherits his uncle's chateau and vineyard in Provence, where he spent much of his childhood. He discovers a new laid-back lifestyle as he tries to renovate the estate to be sold.

title: Wag the Dog
text: Shortly before an election, a spin-doctor and a Hollywood producer join efforts to fabricate a war in order to cover up a presidential sex scandal.

title: Fast Times at Ridgemont High
text: A group of Southern California high school students are enjoying their most important subjects: sex, drugs and rock n' roll.

title: 101 Dalmatians
text: A woman kidnaps puppies to kill them for their fur, but various animals then gang up against her and get their revenge in slapstick fashion.

title: Solaris
text: A troubled psychologist is sent to investigate the crew of an isolated research station orbiting a bizarre planet.

title: World Trade Center
text: Two Port Authority police officers become trapped under the rubble of the World Trade Center.

title: You, Me and Dupree
text: A best man (Wilson) stays on as a houseguest with the newlyweds, much to the couple's annoyance.

title: Bring It On
text: A champion high school cheerleading squad discovers its previous captain stole all their best routines from an inner-city school and must scramble to compete at this year's championships.

title: Elektra
text: Elektra the warrior survives a near-death experience, becomes an assassin-for-hire, and tries to protect her two latest targets, a single father and his young daughter, from a group of supernatural assassins.

title: For Your Eyes Only
text: Agent 007 is assigned to hunt for a lost British encryption device and prevent it from falling into enemy hands.

title: Sixteen Candles
text: A young girl's "sweet sixteenth" birthday becomes anything but special as she suffers from every embarrassment possible.

title: Cop Land
text: The sheriff of a suburban New Jersey community populated by New York City policemen slowly discovers the town is a front for mob connections and corruption.

title: Bronson
text: A young man who was sentenced to seven years in prison for robbing a post office ends up spending three decades in solitary confinement. During this time, his own personality is supplanted by his alter-ego, Charles Bronson.

title: Philomena
text: A world-weary political journalist picks up the story of a woman's search for her son, who was taken away from her decades ago after she became pregnant and was forced to live in a convent.

title: Analyze That
text: Mobster Paul Vitti is released into Dr. Ben Sobol's care, where only more chaos ensues.

title: Under the Skin
text: A mysterious woman seduces lonely men in the evening hours in Scotland. Events lead her to begin a process of self-discovery.

title: The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel
text: British retirees travel to India to take up residence in what they believe is a newly restored hotel. Less luxurious than advertised, the Marigold Hotel nevertheless slowly begins to charm in unexpected ways.

title: Falling Skies
text: Survivors of an alien attack on earth gather together to fight for their lives and fight back.

title: Assault on Precinct 13
text: A police sergeant must rally the cops and prisoners together to protect themselves on New Year's Eve, just as corrupt policeman surround the station with the intent of killing all to keep their deception in the ranks.

title: Touch of Evil
text: A stark, perverse story of murder, kidnapping, and police corruption in a Mexican border town.

title: Cool Runnings
text: When a Jamaican sprinter is disqualified to the Olympic Games, he enlists the help of a dishonored coach to start the first Jamaican Bobsled Team.

title: Hostel: Part II
text: Three American college students studying abroad are lured to a Slovakian hostel, and discover the grim reality behind it.

title: The Doors
text: The story of the famous and influential 1960s rock band and its lead singer and composer, Jim Morrison, from his days as a UCLA film student in Los Angeles, to his untimely death in Paris, France at age 27 in 1971.

title: Felon
text: A family man convicted of killing an intruder must cope with life afterward in the violent penal system.

title: Scooby-Doo
text: After an acrimonious break up, the Mystery Inc. gang are individually brought to an island resort to investigate strange goings on.

title: All About My Mother
text: Young Esteban want to become a writer and also to discover the identity of his father, carefully concealed by the mother Manuela.

title: Into the Woods
text: A witch tasks a childless baker and his wife with procuring magical items from classic fairy tales to reverse the curse put on their family tree.

title: Grandma's Boy
text: A 35 year old video game tester has to move in with his grandma and her two old lady roommates.

title: The Warriors
text: In 1979 a charismatic leader summons the street gangs of New York City in a bid to take it over. When he is killed, The Warriors are falsely blamed and now must fight their way home while every other gang is hunting them down to kill them.

title: Jackass: The Movie
text: Johnny Knoxville and his band of maniacs perform a variety of stunts and gross-out gags on the big screen for the first time.

title: A Walk Among the Tombstones
text: Private investigator Matthew Scudder is hired by a drug kingpin to find out who kidnapped and murdered his wife.

title: Sex Tape
text: A married couple wake up to discover that the sex tape they made the evening before has gone missing, leading to a frantic search for its whereabouts.

title: Yojimbo
text: A crafty ronin comes to a town divided by two criminal gangs and decides to play them against each other to free the town.

title: Persepolis
text: Poignant coming-of-age story of a precocious and outspoken young Iranian girl that begins during the Islamic Revolution.

title: Blended
text: After a bad blind date, a man and woman find themselves stuck together at a resort for families, where their attraction grows as their respective kids benefit from the burgeoning relationship.

title: Home Alone 3
text: Alex Pruitt, a young boy of nine living in Chicago, fend off thieves who seek a top-secret chip in his toy car to support a North Korean terrorist organization's next deed.

title: The Giver
text: In a seemingly perfect community, without war, pain, suffering, differences or choice, a young boy is chosen to learn from an elderly man about the true pain and pleasure of the "real" world.

title: Kiki's Delivery Service
text: A young witch, on her mandatory year of independent life, finds fitting into a new community difficult while she supports herself by running an air courier service.

title: The Quick and the Dead
text: Lady avenger returns to western town owned by a ruthless gunslinger hosting an elimination tournament.

title: Letters to Juliet
text: Sophie dreams of becoming a writer and travels to Verona, Italy where she meets the "Secretaries of Juliet".

title: Sicko
text: A documentary comparing the highly profitable American health care industry to other nations, and HMO horror stories.

title: The Dukes of Hazzard
text: Cousins Bo and Luke Duke, with a little help from their cousin Daisy and Uncle Jesse, egg on the authorities of Hazzard County, Boss Hogg and Sheriff Coltrane.

title: Driving Miss Daisy
text: An old Jewish woman and her African-American chauffeur in the American South have a relationship that grows and improves over the years.

title: Clear and Present Danger
text: CIA Analyst Jack Ryan is drawn into an illegal war fought by the US government against a Colombian drug cartel.

title: Friday
text: Craig and Smokey are two guys in Los Angeles hanging out on their porch on a Friday afternoon, smoking and looking for something to do...

title: Funny Games
text: Two psychopathic young men take a family hostage in their cabin.

title: A Christmas Carol
text: An animated retelling of Charles Dickens' classic novel about a Victorian-era miser taken on a journey of self-redemption, courtesy of several mysterious Christmas apparitions.

title: Bridget Jones: The Edge of Reason
text: After finding love, Bridget Jones questions if she really has everything she's dreamed of having.

title: The Last Emperor
text: The story of the final Emperor of China.

title: Ali G Indahouse
text: Ali G unwittingly becomes a pawn in the evil Chancellor's plot to overthrow the Prime Minister of Great Britain...

title: The Legend of Zorro
text: Despite trying to keep his swashbuckling to a minimum, a threat to California's pending statehood causes the adventure-loving Alejandro de la Vega (Banderas) -- and his wife, Elena (Zeta-Jones) -- to take action.

title: That's My Boy
text: While in his teens, Donny fathered a son, Todd, and raised him as a single parent up until Todd's 18th birthday. Now, after not seeing each other for years, Todd's world comes crashing down when Donny resurfaces just before Todd's wedding.

title: Enemy
text: A man seeks out his exact look-alike after spotting him in a movie.

title: Amour
text: Georges and Anne are an octogenarian couple. They are cultivated, retired music teachers. Their daughter, also a musician, lives in Britain with her family. One day, Anne has a stroke, and the couple's bond of love is severely tested.

title: Secretary
text: A young woman, recently released from a mental hospital, gets a job as a secretary to a demanding lawyer, where their employer-employee relationship turns into a sexual, sadomasochistic one.

title: Thirteen
text: A thirteen-year-old girl's relationship with her mother is put to the test as she discovers drugs, sex, and petty crime in the company of her cool but troubled best friend.

title: The Purge: Anarchy
text: Three groups of people are trying to survive Purge Night, when their stories intertwine and are left stranded in The Purge trying to survive the chaos and violence that occurs.

title: Never Been Kissed
text: A journalist enrolls in her old highschool as part of her research for a story.

title: CSI: Crime Scene Investigation
text: An elite team of police forensic evidence investigation experts work their cases in Las Vegas.

title: Nymphomaniac: Vol. I
text: A self-diagnosed nymphomaniac recounts her erotic experiences to the man who saved her after a beating.

title: Semi-Pro
text: Jackie Moon, the owner-coach-player of the American Basketball Association's Flint Michigan Tropics, rallies his teammates to make their NBA dreams come true

title: Archer
text: At ISIS, an international spy agency, global crises are merely opportunities for its highly trained employees to confuse, undermine, betray and royally screw each other.

title: The Spiderwick Chronicles
text: Upon moving into the run-down Spiderwick Estate with their mother, twin brothers Jared and Simon Grace, along with their sister Mallory, find themselves pulled into an alternate world full of faeries and other creatures.

title: Maid in Manhattan
text: A senatorial candidate falls for a hotel maid, thinking she is a socialite when he sees her trying on a wealthy woman's dress.

title: Nosferatu
text: Vampire Count Orlok expresses interest in a new residence and real estate agent Hutter's wife. Silent classic based on the story "Dracula."

title: The Host
text: A monster emerges from Seoul's Han River and focuses its attention on attacking people. One victim's loving family does what it can to rescue her from its clutches.

title: The Invasion
text: As a Washington psychiatrist unearths the origin of an alien epidemic, she also discovers her son might be the only way it can be stopped.

title: Jingle All the Way
text: A father needs to get a Turbo Man action figure for his son just before Christmas. Unfotunately, every store is sold out of Turbo Man figures, and he must travel all over town and compete with everybody else to find a Turbo Man figure.

title: Battlefield Earth
text: After enslavement & near extermination by an alien race in the year 3000, humanity begins to fight back.

title: Leap Year
text: Anna Brady plans to travel to Dublin, Ireland to propose marriage to her boyfriend Jeremy on Leap Day, because, according to Irish tradition, a man who receives a marriage proposal on a leap day must accept it.

title: 88 Minutes
text: On the day that a serial killer that he helped put away is supposed to be executed, a noted forensic psychologist and college professor receives a call informing him that he has 88 minutes left to live.

title: U-571
text: A German submarine is boarded by disguised American submariners trying to capture their Enigma cipher machine.

title: Incendies
text: Twins journey to the Middle East to discover their family history, and fulfill their mother's last wishes.

title: Blood Simple.
text: A rich but jealous man hires a private investigator to kill his cheating wife and her new man. But, when blood is involved, nothing is simple.

title: Oculus
text: A woman tries to exonerate her brother, who was convicted of murder, by proving that the crime was committed by a supernatural phenomenon.

title: Gosford Park
text: The lives of upstairs guest and downstairs servants at a party in 1932 in a country house in England as they investigate a murder involving one of them.

title: Notes on a Scandal
text: A veteran high school teacher befriends a younger art teacher, who is having an affair with one of her 15-year-old students. However, her intentions with this new "friend" also go well beyond platonic friendship.

title: The Celebration
text: At Helge's 60th birthday party, some unpleasant family truths are revealed.

title: Bad Lieutenant: Port of Call New Orleans
text: Terence McDonagh is a drug- and gambling-addled detective in post-Katrina New Orleans investigating the killing of five Senegalese immigrants.

title: Mean Streets
text: A small-time hood struggles to succeed on the "mean streets" of Little Italy.

title: The Living Daylights
text: James Bond is living on the edge to stop an evil arms dealer from starting another world war. Bond crosses all seven continents in order to stop the evil Whitaker and General Koskov.

title: Delicatessen
text: Post-apocalyptic surrealist black comedy about the landlord of an apartment building who occasionally prepares a delicacy for his odd tenants.

title: They Live
text: A drifter discovers a pair of sunglasses that allow him to wake up to the fact that aliens have taken over the Earth.

title: Around the World in 80 Days
text: A bet pits a British inventor, a Chinese thief, and a French artist on a worldwide adventure that they can circle the globe in 80 days.

title: Safe Haven
text: A young woman with a mysterious past lands in Southport, North Carolina where her bond with a widower forces her to confront the dark secret that haunts her.

title: The Hudsucker Proxy
text: A naive business graduate is installed as president of a manufacturing company as part of a stock scam.

title: Psych
text: A novice sleuth is hired by the police after he cons them into thinking he has psychic powers which help solve crimes. With the assistance of his reluctant best friend, the duo take on a series of complicated cases.

title: Spanglish
text: A woman and her daughter emigrate from Mexico for a better life in America, where they start working for a family where the patriarch is a newly celebrated chef with an insecure wife.

title: Big Momma's House
text: An FBI agent disguises himself as an old lady to protect a beautiful federal witness and her son.

title: Atlantis: The Lost Empire
text: A young adventurer named Milo Thatch joins an intrepid group of explorers to find the mysterious lost continent of Atlantis.

title: Leyla and Mecnun
text: Turkish television comedy series set in Istanbul, Leyla and Mecnun is a surreal and absurd comedy that revolves around the fictional love story between Leyla and Mecnun.

title: An Inconvenient Truth
text: A documentary on Al Gore's campaign to make the issue of global warming a recognized problem worldwide.

title: Outlander
text: During the reign of the Vikings, Kainan, a man from a far-off world, crash lands on Earth, bringing with him an alien predator known as the Moorwen. Though both man and monster are seeking revenge for violence committed against them, Kainan leads the alliance to kill the Moorwen by fusing his advanced technology with the Viking's Iron Age weaponry.

title: Ghosts of Girlfriends Past
text: While attending his brother's wedding, a serial womanizer is haunted by the ghosts of his past girlfriends.

title: Locke
text: Ivan Locke, a dedicated family man and successful construction manager, receives a phone call on the eve of the biggest challenge of his career that sets in motion a series of events that threaten his carefully cultivated existence.

title: Moonraker
text: James Bond investigates the mid-air theft of a space shuttle and discovers a plot to commit global genocide.

title: Blitz
text: A tough cop is dispatched to take down a serial killer who has been targeting police officers.

title: Monster House
text: Three teens discover that their neighbor's house is really a living, breathing, scary monster.

title: Nacho Libre
text: Berated all his life by those around him, a monk follows his dream and dons a mask to moonlight as a Luchador (Mexican wrestler).

title: The Lucky One
text: A Marine travels to Louisiana after serving three tours in Iraq and searches for the unknown woman he believes was his good luck charm during the war.

title: The Smurfs
text: When the evil wizard Gargamel chases the tiny blue Smurfs out of their village, they tumble from their magical world into New York City.

title: King Kong
text: A film crew goes to a tropical island for an exotic location shoot and discovers a colossal giant gorilla who takes a shine to their female blonde star.

title: Scoop
text: An American journalism student in London scoops a big story, and begins an affair with an aristocrat as the incident unfurls.

title: Crazy Heart
text: A faded country music musician is forced to reassess his dysfunctional life during a doomed romance that also inspires him.

title: Youth in Revolt
text: While his trailer trash parents teeter on the edge of divorce, Nick Twisp sets his sights on dream girl Sheeni Saunders, hoping that she'll be the one to take away his virginity.

title: The Black Dahlia
text: Two policemen see their personal and professional lives fall apart in the wake of the "Black Dahlia" murder investigation.

title: Step Up 2: The Streets
text: Romantic sparks occur between two dance students from different backgrounds at the Maryland School of the Arts.

title: Snake Eyes
text: A shady police detective finds himself in the middle of a murder conspiracy at an important boxing match in an Atlantic City casino.

title: A View to a Kill
text: An investigation of a horse-racing scam leads 007 to a mad industrialist who plans to create a worldwide microchip monopoly by destroying California's Silicon Valley.

title: Young Adult
text: Soon after her divorce, a fiction writer returns to her home in small-town Minnesota, looking to rekindle a romance with her ex-boyfriend, who is now happily married and has a newborn daughter.

title: The Last House on the Left
text: After kidnapping and brutally assaulting two young women, a gang unknowingly finds refuge at a vacation home belonging to the parents of one of the victims: a mother and father who devise an increasingly gruesome series of revenge tactics.

title: Biutiful
text: This is the story of Uxbal, a man living in this world, but able to see his death, which guides his every move.

title: The Day the Earth Stood Still
text: An alien lands and tells the people of Earth that they must live peacefully or be destroyed as a danger to other planets.

title: Say Anything...
text: A noble underachiever and a beautiful valedictorian fall in love the summer before she goes off to college.

title: She's All That
text: A high school jock makes a bet that he can turn an unattractive girl into the school's prom queen.

title: Witness
text: A young Amish boy is sole witness to a murder; policeman John Book goes into hiding in Amish country to protect him until the trial.

title: Swingers
text: Wannabe actors become regulars in the stylish neo-lounge scene; Trent teaches his friend Mike the unwritten rules of the scene.

title: Anna Karenina
text: In late-19th-century Russian high society, St. Petersburg aristocrat Anna Karenina enters into a life-changing affair with the dashing Count Alexei Vronsky.

title: Paris, je t'aime
text: Through the neighborhoods of Paris, love is veiled, revealed, imitated, sucked dry, reinvented and awakened.

title: Legend of the Guardians: The Owls of Ga'Hoole
text: When a young owl is abducted by an evil Owl army, he must escape with new-found friends and seek the legendary Guardians to stop the menace.

title: Taking Lives
text: An FBI profiler is called in by French Canadian police to catch a serial killer who takes on the identity of each new victim.

title: My Fair Lady
text: A misogynistic and snobbish phonetics professor agrees to a wager that he can take a flower girl and make her presentable in high society.

title: The 400 Blows
text: Intensely touching story of a misunderstood young adolescent who, left without attention, delves into a life of petty crime.

title: A Perfect Murder
text: A remake of the

title: I Saw the Devil
text: A secret agent exacts revenge on a serial killer through a series of captures and releases.

title: The Mothman Prophecies
text: A reporter is drawn to a small West Virginia town to investigate a series of strange events, including psychic visions and the appearance of bizarre entities.

title: Abduction
text: A thriller centered on a young man who sets out to uncover the truth about his life after finding his baby photo on a missing persons website.

title: Saw 3D: The Final Chapter
text: As a deadly battle rages over Jigsaw's brutal legacy, a group of Jigsaw survivors gathers to seek the support of self-help guru and fellow survivor Bobby Dagen, a man whose own dark secrets unleash a new wave of terror.

title: John Tucker Must Die
text: Three ex-girlfriends of a serial cheater set up their former lover to fall for the new girl in town so they can watch him get his heart broken.

title: Phenomenon
text: An ordinary man sees a bright light descend from the sky, and discovers he now has super-intelligence and telekinesis.

title: Thir13en Ghosts
text: When Cyrus Kriticos, a very rich collector of unique things dies, he leaves it all to his nephew and his family. All including his house, his fortune, and his malicious collection of ghosts!

title: Derailed
text: When two married business executives having an affair are blackmailed by a violent criminal, the two must turn the tables on him to save their families.

title: Another Earth
text: On the night of the discovery of a duplicate Earth in the Solar system, an ambitious young student and an accomplished composer cross paths in a tragic accident.

title: New Year's Eve
text: The lives of several couples and singles in New York intertwine over the course of New Year's Eve.

title: To Rome with Love
text: The lives of some visitors and residents of Rome and the romances, adventures and predicaments they get into.

title: Lolita
text: A middle-aged college professor becomes infatuated with a fourteen-year-old nymphet.

title: Hot Shots! Part Deux
text: "Rambo" parody in which Topper Harley leads a rescue team into Iraq to save Iraqi war prisoners and all of their previous rescue teams.

title: Mississippi Burning
text: Two FBI agents with wildly different styles arrive in Mississippi to investigate the disappearance of some civil rights activists.

title: Doomsday
text: A futuristic action thriller where a team of people work to prevent a disaster threatening the future of the human race.

title: The Pink Panther
text: Bumbling Inspector Clouseau must solve the murder of a famous soccer coach and find out who stole the infamous Pink Panther diamond.

title: The Straight Story
text: An old man makes a long journey by lawn-mover tractor to mend his relationship with an ill brother.

title: A Very Long Engagement
text: Tells the story of a young woman's relentless search for her fiancÃ©, who has disappeared from the trenches of the Somme during World War One.

title: Eraserhead
text: Henry Spencer tries to survive his industrial environment, his angry girlfriend, and the unbearable screams of his newly born mutant child.

title: National Lampoon's Vacation
text: The Griswold family's cross-country drive to the Walley World theme park proves to be much more arduous than they ever anticipated.

title: 40 Days and 40 Nights
text: After a brutal break-up, a young man vows to stay celibate during the forty days of Lent, but finds the girl of his dreams and is unable to do anything about it.

title: The Sea Inside
text: The factual story of Spaniard Ramon Sampedro, who fought a thirty-year campaign in favor of euthanasia and his own right to die.

title: Treasure Planet
text: A Disney animated version of "Treasure Island". The only difference is that the film is set in outer space with alien worlds and other galactic wonders.

title: Awake
text: The story focuses on a man who suffers "anesthetic awareness" and finds himself awake and aware, but paralyzed, during heart surgery. His mother must wrestle with her own demons as a turn of events unfolds around them, while trying to unfold the story hidden behind her son's young wife.

title: Primer
text: Four friends/fledgling entrepreneurs, knowing that there's something bigger and more innovative than the different error-checking devices they've built, wrestle over their new invention.

title: Get Shorty
text: A mobster travels to Hollywood to collect a debt and discovers that the movie business is much the same as his current job.

title: 2 Broke Girls
text: Two young women waitressing at a greasy spoon diner strike up an unlikely friendship in the hopes of launching a successful business - if only they can raise the cash.

title: The Piano
text: A mute woman along with her young daughter, and her prized piano, are sent to 1850s New Zealand for an arranged marriage to a wealthy landowner, and she's soon lusted after by a local worker on the plantation.
The story of Jackie Robinson from his signing with the Brooklyn Dodgers organization in 1945 to his historic 1947 rookie season when he broke the color barrier in Major League Baseball.

title: Mr. Popper's Penguins
text: The life of a businessman begins to change after he inherits six penguins, and as he transforms his apartment into a winter wonderland, his professional side starts to unravel.

title: Centurion
text: A splinter group of Roman soldiers fight for their lives behind enemy lines after their legion is decimated in a devastating guerrilla attack.

title: Journey 2: The Mysterious Island
text: Sean Anderson partners with his mom's husband on a mission to find his grandfather, who is thought to be missing on a mythical island.

title: The O.C.
text: A troubled youth becomes embroiled in the lives of a close-knit group of people in the wealthy, upper-class neighborhood of Newport Beach, Orange County, California.

title: The Manchurian Candidate
text: A former Korean War POW is brainwashed by Communists into becoming a political assassin. But another former prisoner may know how to save him.

title: It
text: In 1960, seven outcast kids known as "The Loser Club" fight an evil demon who poses as a child-killing clown. 30 years later, they are called back to fight the same clown again.

title: The Science of Sleep
text: A man entranced by his dreams and imagination is love-struck with a French woman and feels he can show her his world.

title: Sunshine Cleaning
text: In order to raise the tuition to send her young son to private school, a mom starts an unusual business -- a biohazard removal/crime scene clean-up service -- with her unreliable sister.

title: Kate & Leopold
text: Kate and her actor brother live in N.Y. in the 21st Century. Her ex-boyfriend, Stuart, lives above her apartment...

title: Brother Bear
text: When a young Inuit hunter needlessly kills a bear, he is magically changed into a bear himself as punishment with a talkative cub being his only guide to changing back.

title: Beautiful Creatures
text: Ethan longs to escape his small Southern town. He meets a mysterious new girl, Lena. Together, they uncover dark secrets about their respective families, their history and their town.

title: Look Who's Talking
text: After a single, career-minded woman is left on her own to give birth to the child of a married man, she finds a new romantic chance in a cab driver. Meanwhile the point-of-view of the newborn boy is narrated through voice over.

title: Gremlins 2: The New Batch
text: The Gremlins are back, and this time, they've taken total control over the building of a media mogul.

title: Premonition
text: Depressed housewife learns her husband was killed in a car accident the day previously, awakens the next morning to find him alive and well at home, and then awakens the next day after to a world in which he is still dead.

title: Kingpin
text: A star bowler whose career was prematurely "cut off" hopes to ride a new prodigy to success and riches.

title: American Graffiti
text: A couple of high school grads spend one final night cruising the strip with their buddies before they go off to college.

title: The Wild Bunch
text: An aging group of outlaws look for one last big score as the "traditional" American West is disappearing around them.

title: That Awkward Moment
text: Three best friends find themselves where we've all been - at that confusing moment in every dating relationship when you have to decide "So...where is this going?"

title: October Sky
text: The true story of Homer Hickam, a coal miner's son who was inspired by the first Sputnik launch to take up rocketry against his father's wishes.

title: Into the Blue

text: Set after the events in

text: Sam Childers

title: Thirteen Days
text: A dramatization of President Kennedy's administration's struggle to contain the Cuban Missile Crisis in October of 1962.

title: Takers
text: A group of bank robbers find their multi-million dollar plan interrupted by a hard-boiled detective.

title: A Nightmare on Elm Street 3: Dream Warriors
text: Survivors of undead serial killer Freddy Krueger - who stalks his victims in their dreams - learn to take control of their own dreams in order to fight back.

title: The Whole Ten Yards
text: Jimmy the Tulip's (Willis) quiet new life is shaken up by his old pal Oz (Perry), whose wife (Henstridge) has been kidnapped by a Hungarian mob. The Tulip and his wife Jill (Peet) spring into action.

title: House on Haunted Hill
text: A millionaire offers a group of diverse people $1,000,000 to spend the night in a haunted house with a horrifying past.

title: Best in Show
text: A colorful array of characters competes at a national dog show.

title: The Possession
text: A young girl buys an antique box at a yard sale, unaware that inside the collectible lives a malicious ancient spirit. The girl's father teams with his ex-wife to find a way to end the curse upon their child.

title: The Devil's Backbone
text: After Carlos, a 12-year-old whose father has died in the Spanish Civil War, arrives at an ominous boy's orphanage he discovers the school is haunted and has many dark secrets that he must uncover.

title: The Rules of Attraction
text: The incredibly spoiled and overprivileged students of Camden College are a backdrop for an unusual love triangle between a drug dealer, a virgin and a bisexual classmate.

title: Europa Report
text: An international crew of astronauts undertakes a privately funded mission to search for life on Jupiter's fourth largest moon.

title: Searching for Sugar Man
text: Two South Africans set out to discover what happened to their unlikely musical hero, the mysterious 1970s rock 'n' roller, Rodriguez.

title: My Bloody Valentine
text: Tom returns to his hometown on the tenth anniversary of the Valentine's night massacre that claimed the lives of 22 people. Instead of a homecoming, however, Tom finds himself suspected of committing the murders, and it seems like his old flame is the only one will believes he's innocent.

title: The Ghost and the Darkness
text: Set in 1898, this movie is based on the true story of two lions in Africa that killed 35 people over a nine month period...

title: Nymphomaniac: Vol. II
text: The continuation of Joe's sexually dictated life delves into the darker aspects of her adulthood, obsessions and what led to her being in Seligman's care.

title: American Pie Presents Beta House
text: Erik, and Cooze start college and pledge the Beta House fraternity, presided over by none other than legendary Dwight Stifler...

title: Fish Tank
text: Everything changes for 15-year-old Mia when her mum brings home a new boyfriend.

title: The Condemned
text: Jack Conrad is awaiting the death penalty in a corrupt Central American prison. He is "purchased" by a wealthy television producer and taken to a desolate island where he must fight to the death against nine other condemned killers from all corners of the world, with freedom going to the sole survivor.

title: Indecent Proposal
text: A married woman agrees to have sex with another man for $1,000,000.

title: RV
text: Bob Munro and his dysfunctional family rent an RV for a road trip to the Colorado Rockies, where they ultimately have to contend with a bizarre community of campers.

title: The Astronaut's Wife
text: After an explosion in space and subsequent two-minute radio-out period, two astronauts return home to their wives. Slightly it's revealed that they're not the same as they were.

title: Hoodwinked!
text: The candy recipes of the goody shops have been stolen by the Goody Bandit, and many animals are out of business...

title: Duplex
text: A young couple has a chance to move into a gorgeous duplex in the perfect New York neighborhood. All they have to do is bump off the current tenant, a cute little old lady.

title: Dog Soldiers
text: A routine military exercise turns into a nightmare in the Scotland wilderness.

title: Dark Water
text: A mother and daughter, still wounded from a bitter custody dispute, hole up in a run-down apartment building. Adding further drama to their plight, they are targeted by the ghost of former resident.

title: Wings of Desire
text: An angel tires of overseeing human activity and wishes to become human when he falls in love with a mortal.

title: Stripes
text: Two friends who are dissatisfied with their jobs decide to join the army for a bit of fun.

title: Beethoven
text: A slobbering St. Bernard becomes the center of attention for a loving family, but its veterinarian secretly wants to kill him.

title: Cats & Dogs
text: A look at the top-secret, high-tech espionage war going on between cats and dogs, which their human owners are blissfully unaware of.

title: What a Girl Wants
text: An American teenager learns that her father is a wealthy British politician running for office. Although she is eager to find him, she realizes it could cause a scandal and cost him the election.

title: Benny & Joon
text: A mentally ill young woman finds her love in an eccentric man who models himself after Buster Keaton.

title: The Great Beauty
text: Jep Gambardella has seduced his way through the lavish nightlife of Rome for decades, but after his 65th birthday and a shock from the past, Jep looks past the nightclubs and parties to find a timeless landscape of absurd, exquisite beauty.

title: Quills
text: In a Napoleonic era insane asylum, an inmate, the irrepressible Marquis De Sade, fights a battle of wills against a tyrannically prudish doctor.

title: La Dolce Vita
text: A series of stories following a week in the life of a philandering paparazzo journalist living in Rome.

title: Orphan Black
text: A streetwise hustler is pulled into a compelling conspiracy after witnessing the suicide of a girl who looks just like her.

title: The Majestic
text: Set in 1951, a blacklisted Hollywood writer gets into a car accident, loses his memory and settles down in a small town where he is mistaken for a long-lost son.

title: Out of Time
text: A Florida police chief must solve a vicious double homicide before he himself falls under suspicion.

title: The Legend of Bagger Vance
text: A down-and-out golfer attempts to recover his game and his life with help from a mystical caddy.

title: The Client
text: A young boy who witnessed the suicide of a mafia lawyer hires an attorney to protect him when the district attorney tries to use him to take down a mob family.

title: Shallow Grave
text: Three friends discover their new flatmate dead but loaded with cash.

title: Top Secret!
text: Parody of WWII spy movies in which an American rock and roll singer becomes involved in a Resistance plot to rescue a scientist imprisoned in East Germany.

title: Straw Dogs
text: A young American and his English wife come to rural England and face increasingly vicious local harassment.

title: Wicker Park
text: A young Chicago advertising executive believes a woman he sees in a cafÃ© is his long-lost love. His conviction leads to obsession, as he puts his life on hold to trail her.

title: Waltz with Bashir
text: An Israeli film director interviews fellow veterans of the 1982 invasion of Lebanon to reconstruct his own memories of his term of service in that conflict.

title: Soldier
text: A soldier is dumped on a waste disposal planet and lives among a community of crash survivors on the planet and takes it upon himself to defend his new home when genetic engineered soldiers are ordered to eliminate the crash survivors.

title: Step Up 3D
text: A tight-knit group of New York City street dancers,find themselves pitted against the world's best hip hop dancers in a high-stakes showdown.

title: Harvey
text: Due to his insistence that he has an invisible six-foot rabbit for a best friend, a whimsical middle-aged man is thought by his family to be insane - but he may be wiser than anyone knows.

title: 4 Months, 3 Weeks and 2 Days
text: A woman assists her friend in arranging an illegal abortion in 1980s Romania.

title: Bullitt
text: An all guts, no glory San Francisco cop becomes determined to find the underworld kingpin that killed the witness in his protection.

title: The Remains of the Day
text: A butler who sacrificed body and soul to service in the years post World War I realizes too late how misguided his loyalty has been.

title: Charlie St. Cloud
text: Charlie St. Cloud has been given the gift of seeing his deceased brother, but when a new love interest is in trouble he must choose between saving a life or continuing to see his brother everyday.

title: Friday Night Lights
text: Based on H.G. Bissinger's book, which profiled the economically depressed town of Odessa, Texas and their heroic high school football team, The Permian High Panthers.

title: Deliver Us from Evil
text: New York police officer Ralph Sarchie investigates a series of crimes. He joins forces with an unconventional priest, schooled in the rites of exorcism, to combat the possessions that are terrorizing their city.

title: The Right Stuff
text: The story of the original Mercury 7 astronauts and their macho, seat-of-the-pants approach to the space program.

title: Turner & Hooch
text: A detective must adopt the dog of a dead man to help him find the murderer.

title: Stuck on You
text: Conjoined twins from Martha's Vineyard move to Los Angeles so that one of them can pursue an acting career.

title: Jonah Hex
text: The U.S. military makes a scarred bounty hunter with warrants on his own head an offer he cannot refuse: in exchange for his freedom, he must stop a terrorist who is ready to unleash Hell on Earth.

title: Heartbreakers
text: A mother and daughter con team seduce and scam wealthy men.

title: Coffee and Cigarettes
text: A series of vignettes that all have coffee and cigarettes in common.

title: Girls
text: A comedy about the experiences of a group of girls in their early 20s.

title: The Soloist
text: A Los Angeles journalist befriends a homeless Juilliard-trained musician, while looking for a new article for the paper.

title: We Are Marshall
text: When a plane crash claims the lives of members of the Marshall University football team and some of its fans, the team's new coach and his surviving players try to keep the football program alive.

title: Stepmom
text: A terminally ill mother has to settle on the new woman in her former husband's life who will be their stepmother.

title: The Rainmaker
text: An idealistic young lawyer and his cynical partner take on a powerful law firm representing a corrupt insurance company.

title: Time Bandits
text: A young boy accidentally joins a band of dwarves as they jump from era to era looking for treasure to steal.

title: Duel
text: A business commuter is pursued and terrorized by a malevolent driver of a massive tractor-trailer.

title: Bad Education
text: An examination on the effect of Franco-era religious schooling and sexual abuse on the lives of two longtime friends.

title: Sneakers
text: Complex but lighthearted thriller about computers and cryptography, government and espionage, secrets and deception and betrayal.

title: The Wicker Man
text: A police sergeant is sent to a Scottish island village in search of a missing girl whom the townsfolk claim never existed. Stranger still are the rites that take place there.

title: Animal Kingdom
text: A seventeen year-old navigates his survival amongst an explosive criminal family and the detective who thinks he can save him.

title: Original Sin
text: A young man is plunged into a life of subterfuge, deceit and mistaken identity in pursuit of a femme fatale whose heart is never quite within his grasp. Remake of FranÃ§ois Truffaut's 1969 film 'Mississippi Mermaid'

title: Cassandra's Dream
text: The tale of two brothers with serious financial woes. When a third party proposes they turn to crime, things go bad and the two become enemies.

title: The World's Fastest Indian
text: The life story of New Zealander Burt Munro, who spent years building a 1920 Indian motorcycle -- a bike which helped him set the land-speed world record at Utah's Bonneville Salt Flats in 1967.

title: Last Man Standing
text: A drifting gunslinger-for-hire finds himself in the middle of an ongoing war between the Irish and Italian mafia in a Prohibition era ghost town.

title: Bringing Up Baby
text: While trying to secure a $1 million donation for his museum, a befuddled paleontologist is pursued by a flighty and often irritating heiress and her pet leopard "Baby."

title: Dream House
text: Soon after moving into their seemingly idyllic new home, a family learns of a brutal crime committed against former residents of the dwelling.

title: Oldboy
text: Obsessed with vengeance, a man sets out to find out why he was kidnapped and locked into solitary confinement for twenty years without reason.

title: Shadow of a Doubt
text: A young woman discovers her visiting "Uncle Charlie" may not be the man he seems to be.

title: Badlands
text: An impressionable teen girl from a dead-end town and her older greaser boyfriend go on a killing spree in the South Dakota badlands.

title: La Strada
text: A care-free girl is sold to a traveling entertainer, consequently enduring physical and emotional pain along the way.

title: My Blueberry Nights
text: A young woman takes a soul-searching journey across America to resolve her questions about love while encountering a series of offbeat characters along the way.

title: The Eye
text: A woman receives an eye transplant that allows her to see into the supernatural world.

title: Kinsey
text: A look at the life of Alfred Kinsey, a pioneer in the area of human sexuality research, whose 1948 publication "Sexual Behavior in the Human Male" was one of the first recorded works that saw science address sexual behavior.

title: Casanova
text: Heath Ledger plays the fabled romantic as a man who, after failing to win the affection of a particular Venetian woman, strives to discover the real meaning of love.

title: The Fog
text: Legend says that Antonio Bay was built in 1880 with blood money obtained from shipwrecked lepers but no one believes it. On the eve of the town's centennial many plan to attend the celebrations, including the murdered lepers.

title: Formula 51
text: An American master chemist plans to score big on a once in a lifetime drug deal. All does not go as planned and he is soon entangled in a web of deceit.

title: Crocodile Dundee II
text: Australian outback expert protects his New York love from gangsters who've followed her down under.

title: Take Me Home Tonight
text: Four years after graduation, an awkward high school genius uses his sister's boyfriend's Labor Day party as the perfect opportunity to make his move on his high school crush.

title: The Rocketeer
text: A young pilot stumbles onto a prototype jetpack that allows him to become a high flying masked hero.

title: Stalag 17
text: When two escaping American World War II prisoners are killed, the German POW camp barracks black marketeer, J.J. Sefton, is suspected of being an informer.

title: Ella Enchanted
text: Ella is under a spell to be constantly obedient, a fact she must hide from her new step-family in order to protect the prince of the land, her friend for whom she's falling.

title: Timecop
text: An officer for a security agency that regulates time travel, must fend for his life against a shady politician who has a tie to his past.

title: The Love Guru
text: Pitka an American raised outside of his country by gurus, returns to the States in order to break into the self-help business. His first challenge: To settle the romantic troubles and subsequent professional skid of a star hockey player whose wife left him for a rival athlete.

title: Cocoon
text: When a group of trespassing seniors swim in a pool containing alien cocoons, they find themselves energized with youthful vigour.

title: The Guest
text: A soldier introduces himself to the Peterson family, claiming to be a friend of their son who died in action. After the young man is welcomed into their home, a series of accidental deaths seem to be connected to his presence.

title: Sympathy for Mr. Vengeance
text: A recently laid off factory worker kidnaps his former boss' daughter, hoping to use the ransom money to pay for his sister's kidney transplant.

title: The Dilemma
text: A man discovers that his best friend's wife is having an affair.

title: Hesher
text: A young boy has lost his mother and is losing touch with his father and the world around him. Then he meets Hesher who manages to make his life even more chaotic.

title: The Devil's Own
text: A police officer uncovers the real identity of his house-guest, an I.R.A. terrorist in hiding.

title: Hart's War
text: A law student becomes a lieutenant during World War II, is captured and asked to defend a black prisoner of war falsely accused of murder.

title: The Sentinel
text: A Secret Service agent is framed as the mole in an assassination attempt on the President. He must clear his name and foil another assassination attempt while on the run from a Secret Service Protective Intelligence Division agent.

title: To Catch a Thief
text: When a reformed jewel thief is suspected of returning to his former occupation, he must ferret out the real thief in order to prove his innocence.

title: Lords of Dogtown
text: The film follows the surf and skateboarding trends that originated in Venice, California during the 1970's.

title: Great Expectations
text: Modernization of Charles Dickens classic story finds the hapless Finn as a painter in New York pursuing his unrequited and haughty childhood love.

title: The Proposition
text: A lawman apprehends a notorious outlaw and gives him nine days to kill his older brother, or else they'll execute his younger brother.

title: Legend
text: A young man must stop the Lord of Darkness from both destroying daylight and marrying the woman he loves.

title: Fruitvale Station
text: The story of Oscar Grant III, a 22-year-old Bay Area resident, who crosses paths with friends, enemies, family, and strangers on the last day of 2008.

title: Paris, Texas
text: A man is found in the desert after four years.

title: Queen of the Damned
text: The vampire Lestat becomes a rock star whose music wakes up the queen of all vampires.

title: Stand Up Guys
text: A pair of aging stickup men try to get the old gang back together for one last hurrah before one of the guys takes his last assignment - to kill his comrade.

title: Murder by Numbers
text: Two gifted high school students execute a "perfect" murder - then become engaged in an intellectual contest with a seasoned homicide detective.

title: The Sisterhood of the Traveling Pants
text: Four best girlfriends hatch a plan to stay connected with one another as their lives start off in different directions: they pass around a pair of secondhand jeans that fits each of their bodies perfectly.

title: Senna
text: A documentary on Brazilian Formula One racing driver Ayrton Senna, who won the F1 world championship three times before his death at age 34.

title: Like Crazy
text: A British college student falls for an American student, only to be separated from him when she's banned from the U.S. after overstaying her visa.

title: Wolf
text: Publisher Will Randall becomes a werewolf and has to fight to keep his job.

title: Eight Legged Freaks
text: A variety of horrible poisonous spiders get exposed to a noxious chemical that causes them to grow to monumental proportions.

title: Secondhand Lions
text: A coming-of-age story about a shy, young boy sent by his irresponsible mother to spend the summer with his wealthy, eccentric uncles in Texas.

title: Just My Luck
text: Manhattanite Ashley is known to many as the luckiest woman around. After a chance encounter with a down-and-out young man, however, she realizes that she's swapped her fortune for his.

title: LOL
text: As a new year at school begins, Lola's heart is broken by her boyfriend, though soon she's surprised by her best friend, promising musician Kyle, who reveals his feelings for her.

title: Bulletproof Monk
text: Based on the very underground comic book, a Tibetan monk becomes a mentor to a young street kid whom he can teach to protect a scroll.

title: Penny Dreadful
text: Explorer Sir Malcolm Murray, American gunslinger Ethan Chandler, and others unite to combat supernatural threats in Victorian London.

title: The American President
text: Comedy-drama about a widowed U.S. president and a lobbyist who fall in love. It's all above-board, but "politics is perception" and sparks fly anyway.

title: Hudson Hawk
text: A cat burglar is forced to steal Da Vinci works of art for a world domination plot.

title: 15 Minutes
text: A homicide detective and a fire marshall must stop a pair of murderers who commit videotaped crimes to become media darlings.

title: Soylent Green
text: With the world ravaged by the greenhouse effect and overpopulation, an NYPD detective investigates the murder of a CEO with ties to the world's main food supply.

title: The Mission
text: 18th century Spanish Jesuits try to protect a remote South American Indian tribe in danger of falling under the rule of pro-slavery Portugal.

title: In the Loop
text: The US President and UK Prime Minister fancy a war. But not everyone agrees that war is a good thing...

title: Alfie
text: A cockney womanizer learns the hard way about the dangers of his actions.

title: Show Me Love
text: Two teenage girls in small-town Sweden. Elin is beautiful, popular, and bored with life. Agnes is friendless, sad, and secretly in love with Elin.

title: Becoming Jane
text: A biographical portrait of a pre-fame Jane Austen and her romance with a young Irishman.

title: Shine
text: Pianist David Helfgott, driven by his father and teachers, has a breakdown. Years later he returns to the piano, to popular if not critical acclaim.

title: Cry-Baby
text: In 1950s Baltimore, a bad-boy with a heart of gold wins the love of a good-girl, whose boyfriend sets out for revenge.

title: Chaos
text: Two cops, a rookie and a grizzled vet, pursue an accomplished bank robber.

title: Anatomy of a Murder
text: In a murder trial, the defendant says he suffered temporary insanity after the victim raped his wife. What is the truth, and will he win his case?

title: Marathon Man
text: A graduate history student is unwittingly caught in the middle of an international conspiracy involving stolen diamonds, an exiled Nazi war criminal, and a rogue government agent.

title: Jeepers Creepers II
text: Set a few days after the original, a championship basketball team's bus is attacked by The Creeper, the winged, flesh-eating terror, on the last day of his 23-day feeding frenzy.

title: Pushing Daisies
text: A pie-maker, with the power to bring dead people back to life, solves murder mysteries with his alive-again childhood sweetheart, a cynical private investigator, and a lovesick waitress.

title: The Longest Day
text: The events of D-Day, told on a grand scale from both the Allied and German points of view.

title: American Splendor
text: An original mix of fiction and reality illuminates the life of comic book hero everyman Harvey Pekar.

title: Orange County
text: A guidance counselor mistakenly sends out the wrong transcripts to Stanford University under the name of an over-achieving high schooler.

title: The Awakening
text: In 1921, England is overwhelmed by the loss and grief of World War I. Hoax exposer Florence Cathcart visits a boarding school to explain sightings of a child ghost. Everything she believes unravels as the 'missing' begin to show themselves.

title: Rust and Bone
text: Put in charge of his young son, Alain leaves Belgium for Antibes to live with his sister and her husband as a family. Alain's bond with Stephanie, a killer whale trainer, grows deeper after Stephanie suffers a horrible accident.

title: Ghosts of Mars
text: Years in the future, a Martian police unit is sent to pick up a highly dangerous criminal at a remote mining post. Upon arrival, the cops find that the post has become a charnel house.

title: Suspiria
text: A newcomer to a fancy ballet academy gradually comes to realize that the school is a front for something far more sinister and supernatural amidst a series of grisly murders.

title: Step Up Revolution
text: Emily arrives in Miami with aspirations to become a professional dancer. She sparks with Sean, the leader of a dance crew whose neighborhood is threatened by Emily's father's development plans.

title: Copycat
text: An agoraphobic psychologist and a female detective must work together to take down a serial killer who copies serial killers from the past.

title: Duplicity
text: Two ex-government agents turned rival industrial spies have to be at the top of their game when one of their companies prepares to launch a major product. However, they distract each other in more ways than one.

title: The Gods Must Be Crazy
text: A comic allegory about a traveling Bushman who encounters modern civilization and its stranger aspects, including a clumsy scientist and a band of revolutionaries.

title: Session 9
text: Tensions rise within an asbestos cleaning crew as they work in an abandoned mental hospital with a horrific past that seems to be coming back.

title: Gigli
text: The violent story about how a criminal lesbian, a tough-guy hit-man with a heart of gold, and a mentally challenged man came to be best friends through a hostage.

title: U Turn
text: A young punk drifter heading to Vegas to pay off his gambling debt before the Russian mafia kills him, is forced to stop in a Arizona town where everything that can go wrong, does go wrong for him.

title: CSI: Miami
text: The cases of the Miami-Dade, Florida police department's Crime Scene Investigations unit.

title: Batman: The Animated Series
genre: [u'Animation', u'Action', u'Adventure', u'Crime', u'Drama', u'Fantasy', u'Mystery', u'Romance', u'Sci-Fi', u'Thriller']
text: The Dark Knight battles crime in Gotham City with occasional help from Robin and Batgirl.

title: Legally Blonde 2: Red, White & Blonde
text: Elle Woods heads to Washington D.C. to join the staff of a congresswoman in order to pass a bill to ban animal testing.

title: White Noise
text: An architect's desire to speak with his wife from beyond the grave, becomes an obsession with supernatural repercussions.

title: Scandal
text: A former White House Communications Director starts her own crisis management firm only to realize her clients are not the only ones with secrets.

title: Transsiberian
text: A Trans-Siberian train journey from China to Moscow becomes a thrilling chase of deception and murder when an American couple encounters a mysterious pair of fellow travelers.

title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles II: The Secret of the Ooze
text: The Turtles and the Shredder battle once again, this time for the last cannister of the ooze that created the Turtles, which Shredder wants to create an army of new mutants.

title: Sleepy Hollow
text: Ichabod Crane is resurrected and pulled two and a half centuries through time to unravel a mystery that dates all the way back to the founding fathers.

title: The Chorus
text: The new teacher at a severely administered boys' boarding school works to positively affect the students' lives through music.

title: Beavis and Butt-Head Do America
text: The dimwitted teen duo of Beavis and Butt-Head travel across America in search of their stolen television set.

title: The Legend of Hercules
text: The origin story of the the mythical Greek hero. Betrayed by his stepfather, the King, and exiled and sold into slavery because of a forbidden love, Hercules must use his formidable powers to fight his way back to his rightful kingdom.

title: Rent
text: This is the film version of the Pulitzer and Tony Award winning musical about Bohemians in the East Village of New York City struggling with life, love and AIDS, and the impacts they have on America.

title: The Dead Zone
text: A man awakens from a coma to discover he has a psychic detective ability.

title: Zookeeper
text: A group of zoo animals decide to break their code of silence in order to help their lovable zoo keeper find love -- without opting to leave his current job for something more illustrious.

title: The Mighty Ducks
text: A self-centered lawyer is sentenced to community service coaching a rag tag youth hockey team.

title: Sexy Beast
text: Brutal gangster Don Logan recruits "retired" safecracker Gal for one last job, but it goes badly for both of them.

title: Mary Shelley's Frankenstein
text: When the brilliant but unorthodox scientist Victor Frankenstein rejects the artificial man that he has created, the Creature escapes and later swears revenge.

title: The Jerk
text: An idiotic man struggles to make it through life on his own in St. Louis.

title: The Killing Fields
text: A photographer is trapped in Cambodia during tyrant Pol Pot's bloody "Year Zero" cleansing campaign, which claimed the lives of two million "undesirable" civilians.

title: The Good Wife
text: Alicia has been a good wife to her husband, a former state's attorney. After a very humiliating sex and corruption scandal, he is behind bars. She must now provide for her family and returns to work as a litigator in a law firm.

title: The Pledge
text: A retiring police chief pledges to catch the killer of a young child.

title: Porco Rosso
text: The adventures of "Porco Rosso", a veteran WW1 pilot in 1930s Italy, who has been cursed to look like an anthropomorphic pig.

title: The Matador
text: A globetrotting hitman and a crestfallen businessman meet in a hotel bar in Mexico City in an encounter that draws them together in a way neither expected.

title: Nikita
text: A rogue assassin returns to take down the secret organization that trained her.

title: Ichi the Killer
text: As sadomasochistic yakuza enforcer Kakihara searches for his missing boss he comes across Ichi, a repressed and psychotic killer who may be able to inflict levels of pain that Kakihara has only dreamed of.

title: Drinking Buddies
text: Luke and Kate are coworkers at a brewery who spend their nights drinking and flirting heavily. One weekend away together with their significant others proves who really belongs together and who doesn't.

title: Dennis the Menace
text: When his parents have to go out of town, Dennis stays with Mr. and Mrs. Wilson. The little menace is driving Mr. Wilson crazy, but Dennis is just trying to be helpful. Even to the thief who's arrived in town.

title: Continuum
text: A detective from the year 2077 finds herself trapped in present day Vancouver and searching for ruthless criminals from the future.

title: Bernie
text: In small-town Texas, an affable mortician strikes up a friendship with a wealthy widow, though when she starts to become controlling, he goes to great lengths to separate himself from her grasp.

title: Cowboy Bebop
text: The futuristic misadventures and tragedies of an easygoing bounty hunter and his partners.

title: Vampires
text: A vengeful vampire slayer must retrieve an ancient Catholic relic that, should it be acquired by vampires, will allow them to endure sunlight.

title: Spy Kids 2: Island of Lost Dreams
text: The Cortez siblings set out for a mysterious island, where they encounter a genetic scientist and a set of rival spy kids.

title: Star Trek
text: Captain James T. Kirk and the crew of the Starship Enterprise explore the Galaxy and defend the United Federation of Planets.

title: Sabrina
text: A playboy becomes interested in the daughter of his family's chauffeur. But it's his more serious brother who would be the better man for her.

title: Open Water
text: Based on the true story of two scuba divers accidentally stranded in shark infested waters after their tour boat has left.

title: The General's Daughter
text: When the daughter of a well-known and well-respected base commander is murdered, an undercover detective is summoned to look into the matter and finds a slew of cover-ups at West Point.

title: Star Trek V: The Final Frontier
text: Captain Kirk and his crew must deal with Mr. Spock's long-lost half-brother who hijacks the Enterprise for an obsessive search for God at the center of the galaxy.

title: W.
text: A chronicle on the life and presidency of

title: Hawaii Five-0
text: Steve McGarrett returns home to Oahu, in order to find his father's killer. The governor offers him the chance to run his own task force (Five-0). Steve's team is joined by Chin Ho Kelly, Danny "Danno" Williams, and Kono Kalakaua.

title: Lions for Lambs
text: Injuries sustained by two Army rangers behind enemy lines in Afghanistan set off a sequence of events involving a congressman, a journalist and a professor.

title: The Brothers Bloom
